Who is in charge of what? (The Workflow)
Step Who does it? What happens?

1. Trigger Your Backend Sees a user clicked "Sync." It sends a request to your always-running Playwright script.
2. Connect Playwright Script Calls chromium.connectOverCDP(). It connects to the Warm Browserless container instantly.
3. Logic Playwright Script Navigates to /login. It notices the user isn't logged in.
4. Notify Playwright Script Sends a message back: "Hey, I need a human. Tell them to go to https://.../debugger/?id=USER_123."
5. Login The User Opens that link in their browser. They see the Facebook login page, they type their password, and hit enter.
6. Finish Playwright Script It's been "watching" the whole time. As soon as it sees the login worked, it automatically moves to Marketplace.
   Why this is better for you:
   Zero wait time: The user clicks "Sync" and the login screen appears immediately.

Less Code: You delete all the xvfb, x11vnc, and novnc stuff from your Dockerfile. Browserless handles the video stream for you.

Stability: Caddy won't lose connection because the container never restarts.

